    "This is partly due to genetic differences between adult and pAML 4, the rarity of the disease and a shortage of clinical outcome studies related to genetic alterations.",
    "To clarify the genomic landscape of pAML and its association with clinical outcomes, we characterized 887 cases of pAML by transcriptome and genome profiling.",
    "These analyses resulted in 23 molecular categories, defined by mutually exclusive gene alterations and specific expression profiles that show unique biological and mutational characteristics.",
    "These molecular categories have predictive value regarding clinical outcomes that can be leveraged to establish a framework for diagnosis and outcome prediction.",
